Copilot said: Traffic Manager Routing Methods

Priority Routing → Primary endpoint handles traffic; secondary endpoint used during failover.
Weighted Routing → Traffic distributed based on assigned weights (e.g., 70% / 30%).
Performance Routing → Directs users to the endpoint with the lowest network latency.
Geographic Routing → Routes users based on geographic region/country.
MultiValue Routing → Returns multiple healthy endpoints in the DNS response.
Subnet Routing → Routes requests based on the source IP address range/subnet.

Interview One-Liners

Priority → Active-Passive DR setup.
Weighted → Traffic splitting between environments.
Performance → Nearest/fastest endpoint.
Geographic → Region-based user routing.
MultiValue → Multiple endpoints for availability.
Subnet → Route based on client IP range.


